{"id":14881852,"mediaExerciseId":"28714b12-473b-45e7-beb6-a7ddcf181031","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"24","chapterTitle":"Options and Corporate Finance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"24.2","sectionTitle":"Fundamentals of Option Valuation","pageNumber":801,"solutions":[{"id":5991382,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will learn about call option.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define call option.\n\n**Call Option** is the right of a holder to buy a stock.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/50516e8042522fd09f2c1fc20728a0fa/67beda60b7a5cd5c16e57d80b0d28cc1/lateximg_large.png","width":634},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/50516e8042522fd09f2c1fc20728a0fa/67beda60b7a5cd5c16e57d80b0d28cc1/lateximg.png","width":316}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"### Value of a call option at expiration\n\nIf the stock price at the time of expiration is less than the exercise price, then the value of a call option at the end is zero. If not, then the value of the option is the stock price at expiration less the exercise price.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/50516e8042522fd09f2c1fc20728a0fa/60658e85d4f4e523b24798aaf4bfbfd7/lateximg_large.png","width":732},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/50516e8042522fd09f2c1fc20728a0fa/60658e85d4f4e523b24798aaf4bfbfd7/lateximg.png","width":366}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"### The upper and lower bounds on the value of a call option anytime before expiration\n\nThe upper bound on the value of a call option is the current stock price, and the lower bound is the current stock price less the exercise price.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"### If the stock price is certain to be greater than the exercise price on a call option, what is the value of the call.\n\nIf the stock price is certain to be greater than the exercise price on a call option, then it is called **in-the-money**. The value of the call is called the intrinsic value.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"ea2039d0-8008-480e-8c61-a9934ecb8eb8","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881854,"exerciseName":"4","page":807,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d4cc284f-276e-40f9-a7ba-b6d1ee2cbdf2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-24-exercises-4-d4cc284f-276e-40f9-a7ba-b6d1ee2cbdf2"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881851,"exerciseName":"1","page":796,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"68d159fd-ca35-4831-9a75-d186ffdc